svg.title: GuixSD Panel for a SLiM Theme

cc:Work.dc:title: GuixSD Panel for a SLiM Theme
cc:Work.dc:description: A GuixSD panel image for the SLiM login manager.

text.tspan: This image is used as the Panel for a SLiM theme. More information about SLiM themes is available in the
THEME file in the latest slim-x.y.z.tar.gz tarball which is available at:
1. Hide the following layers: Username label, Waves, Colored lights, Background. These layers are used only
for testing the panel against a background and are not necessary in the exported image.
2. Make sure the following layers are visible: GuixSD logo, Input box, Panel area.
3. Unlock the "Panel area" layer. Select it and click on the canvas. Then press Ctrl+A. A transparent
rectangle is selected. This rectangle is used to indicate Inkscape the area of the image that needs to be
4. Click the Export button. In the Export area section, "Selection" should be active. In the Bitmap size section,
width should be 720 px, height is 420 px, and dpi is 90. Filename should be "panel.png".
